{"key":"post-20959045","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>20959045</id>\n<content>I met an &lt;i&gt;agaricus blazei&lt;/i&gt; grower several years ago who would make up a few hundred substrates in turkey tins covered with foil.&amp;nbsp; He'd place them on the shelves in his insulated grow room and then set up two of those construction heaters(salamanders) just outside the building to blow in heat.&amp;nbsp; He could get the whole building up to around 160F or so where he'd leave it overnight.&amp;nbsp; This also served to kill off mites, gnats, etc., between cropping cycles.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>20959097</next>\n<prev>20959041</prev>\n<first>20822448</first>\n<last>27653241</last>\n<when>1418263630</when>\n<utime>12/11/14 04:07 AM</utime>\n</post>"}